Vice President Biden will be traveling to Perrysburg, Ohio, to chair the next meeting of the White House Task Force on Middle Class Families. The meeting will focus on promoting American manufacturing in the 21st century. The Vice President will lead a discussion among experts and the public on the state of manufacturing, how the administration is supporting manufacturing communities during tough economic times, and what they are doing to promote manufacturing in the current economy. Secretary of Commerce Gary Locke, Ohio Governor Ted Strickland, Director of Recovery for Auto Communities and Workers Ed Montgomery, and other local officials will also be in attendance. The event is open to the public, but tickets are limited. Media must RSVP to attend. The event will take place on Tuesday, June 23rd, at the Willard & Kelsey Solar Group in Perrysburg, Ohio.